gomodel:SYNGO_1061  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The work uses antibodies designed to recognize a unique splice variant or one recognizing the predicted intracellular C-terminal common to all splice variants. Immunoreactivities overlap with synaptic marker PSD-95 in the retina and with SNAP-25 with auditory and vestibular system. This place the immunoreactivity in synaptic regions occupied by photoreceptor and hair cells. The quality and/or difficulty of generating antibody controls, the complexity of the gene splicing and the definition of synaptic staining suggest evidence for synaptic staining.. Experimental description: Material and methods: immunohistology of mouse retina.........Immunofluorescence of mouse inner ear..... Primate tissue was also used in the publication but figures used for the annotation were from mice." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1061" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

